cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new tracker design, which involves classification and target state estimation, and introduces several novel techniques to improve tracking performance. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on several benchmark datasets, which indicates that it may also belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
